<br>
I am currently specced 50 Axe, 44 Left Axe, 37 Parry<br>
<br>
After 1.62 I was think of going to 50 Axe, 50 LA and rest in parry (27 I think) in order to try and maxmimise my damage. The 50 LA style will chain off the Snowsquall/icy brilliance chain, which is a rear positional style and the whole chain has had its damage upped after the LA reduction. In Pve, i only really get to do the snowsquall/IcyBrilliance after evading and doing comeback/frosty gaze (stuns target). Get me so far?<br>
<br>
I've been reading a bit more into it and it occurs to me that as my LA style damage will be lower, I will need to try and stay alive longer in order to get a kill. I reckon the only way to do this is to either parry or evade more. In order to evade more I would need to put my Qui up, which would lower my damage per hit...so not too keen on that. I could, however, put parry up and spec 44Axe, 44LA, 44Parry...this would mean parrying more but the parry chain (polar light/frost shadow) is only two styles   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
What if i went 44hammer, 44LA, 44parry...The hammer style crushing blow is usable when you parry and stuns the target which leaves me open to do snowsquall/IcyBrilliance. Or the anytime hammer chain Runiner/Demolish stuns the target allowing me to do the rear positional left axe chain.<br>
<br>
What do you think? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yllmar>Yllmar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://webpages.charter.net/yllmar/images/redball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#000000>(7/1/03 6:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=119.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://webpages.charter.net/yllmar/images/photo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: what to do after 1.62</span><hr size=1> I would try it out on Pendragon first. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yllmar>Yllmar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://webpages.charter.net/yllmar/images/redball.gif" BORDER=0> at: 7/1/03 6:01 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vawl>vawl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#000000>(7/1/03 6:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=119.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> what to do after 1.62</span><hr size=1> I'm based on Excalibur in the UK...can i still copy a char to Pendragon?? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=yllmar>Yllmar</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://webpages.charter.net/yllmar/images/redball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertit