At any rate, I know 44/44/44 is a viable spec, and quite a few Berserkers go that route.  Of course, the standard is 50/50/28 for the best damage output.<br>
<br>
My Berkserker is specced at 50/48/32 Left Axe/Axe/Parry.  I only use Left Axe styles, and for baseline damage I rely on bonuses to get my Axe skill beyond 50.  I wanted to parry a little more than the average Berserker.<br>
<br>
At 44/44/44, you're giving up a couple of level 50 styles, but I don't think you're going to suffer in the damage department <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>that</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> much, if any at all.. and you should parry like a fiend. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=araolath>Araolath</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#000000>(7/1/03 12:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=119.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Speccing</span><hr size=1> I've been a 50/50/28 Hammer Zerker for a very long time now, and I've never felt like speccing around a patch is a good idea. I think 44 Parry is nice for PvE and dueling, but it wont really help you in RvR. That's mainly because when things go bad in RvR they go VERY bad, so 16 pts (+8%) to Parry isn't going to help much when your group gets mezzed and there's 3 tanks and a caster lighting you up. The way I see it, as a Light Tank I have one function, to deal as much damage as quickly as possible. Being 50/50/28 makes me quite lopsided towards offense and shorts me on defense, but if I wanted a defensive tank I'd roll a Warrior. Also, consider the benefits of SC and RR bonus, I'm currently sporting 50+14 HAmmer, 50+14 Left Axe, and 28+14 Parry. the over speecing in Hammer ups my dmg variance by 1% for every 3pts, so my dmg range is 104%-154% which is nice, the overspec also increases your to-hit percentage which is very nice in this age of maxxed resists. If you spend the RA pts to get Dodger 2 you'll evade enought that you'll never miss the parry. BTW, according to testing by several Bezerkers +75 Qui will only decrease dmg over a 2 minute period by about 5%, that's due to the fact that styling works like a DPS add. In theory your style bonus damage over time wont change, the hits are smaller but you hit more often, but like I said field testing shows about a 5% dropoff, could be partially due to the 'slow weapon bonus' that Mythic has never explained fully. In return for this 5% dmg loss you get +4% to your evade chance and you get more swings in, which minimizes the loss in case you miss. If you get one swing every 4s thats 15 swings in 60s, if you swing every 1.5s thats 40 swings in 60s; so every missed hit with 4s SPD represents a 6.67% loss to your dmg output, whereas the same miss only costs you 2.5% of your dmg output at 1.5s SPD. Also worth mentioning is that your base(unstyled damage) is not effected my attack speed modifiers such as haste or quickness, it is purely a product of your  unmodified weapon SPD average.<br>
<br>
Hope thats helpful! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vawl>vawl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#000000>(7/2/03 12:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=119.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> defense/attack</span><hr size=1> Thanks for the ideas Araolath. As I want to change from Axe to hammer spec when 1.62 hits the european servers, I think I'll use my single line respec to spec out of axe. So i'll move from 50axe/44LA/37parry to 44/44/44 initially and see how it goes. The main reason for wanting to try this is that I do quite alot of rvr in small guild groups, i.e 2/3 people...normally zerker/warrior/SB...however, the albs/hibs always seem to go for me, cause I'm a troll, so being a light tank doesnt really apply. My main goal is to last out the fight in order to allow the other 2 guildies to kill the enemy!<br>
